{
  "local_port": 42210,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can apply for residency certificate in India?",
  "response": "A residency certificate is issued to prove that an individual is a resident of a particular state in India. The process for obtaining a residency certificate may vary slightly from state to state, but generally follows a similar procedure. Below is a step-by-step guide to applying for a residency certificate in India:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Determine Eligibility**\nResidency certificates are typically issued to individuals who have been residing in a particular state for a certain period (e.g., 1\u20135 years, depending on the state). You must provide proof of residence during this period.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Required Documents**\nPrepare the necessary documents, which may include:\n- Proof of identity (e.g., Aadhaar card, voter ID, passport)\n- Proof of residence (e.g., rental agreement, electricity bill, water bill, ration card)\n- Passport-sized photographs\n- Application form (available online or at the government office)\n- Affidavit (if required by the state)\n- Any additional documents specified by the state government\n\n---\n\n### **3. Obtain the Application Form**\n- Visit the official website of your state\u2019s Revenue Department or e-District portal.\n- Download the application form for a residency certificate.\n- Alternatively, you can collect the form from the local Tehsil office, Revenue Department, or District Customer Service Center.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Fill Out the Application Form**\nFill in the required details in the form, such as:\n- Personal information (name, address, date of birth, etc.)\n- Details of residence (address, duration of stay)\n- Reason for applying (if applicable)\n\n---\n\n### **5. Submit the Application**\n- Submit the completed application form along with the required documents to the designated office (e.g., Tehsil office, District Revenue Office, or online portal).\n- Pay the applicable fee, if any. Fees vary by state.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Verification Process**\n- A government official may visit your residence to verify the details provided in the application.\n- Ensure that all documents are genuine and accurate to avoid delays.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Receive the Certificate**\n- Once the verification is complete, the residency certificate will be issued. You may receive it via:\n  - Online download (if applied through an e-portal)\n  - In-person collection from the government office\n  - Postal delivery (in some states)\n\n---\n\n### **8. Online Application (Optional)**\nMany states offer online application facilities through their e-District portals. To apply online:\n- Visit your state\u2019s e-District or Revenue Department website.\n- Register and log in to the portal.\n- Fill out the online application form and upload the required documents.\n- Pay the fee online (if applicable).\n- Track the application status online.\n\n---\n\n### **Contact Information**\nIf you face any issues or need clarification:\n- Visit the local Tehsil office or Revenue Department.\n- Check your state\u2019s official website for specific guidelines.\n\n---\n\n### **Note:**\nThe process and requirements may vary slightly depending on the state. Always refer to the official guidelines of your state\u2019s Revenue Department or e-District portal for accurate information.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
